Blog infrastructure is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:

**Already existed (from prior work):**
- `lib/blog.ts` — `getAllPosts`, `getPostBySlug`, `getAllTags` with bilingual frontmatter support
- `components/blog/MDXComponents.tsx` — styled overrides for h1-h3, p, a, code, pre, blockquote, lists, tables
- `app/blog/page.tsx` — post listing with `BlogList` client component for tag filtering
- `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` — `generateStaticParams`, `generateMetadata`, prev/next navigation
- `app/blog/[slug]/BlogPostPage.tsx` — post layout with TOC sidebar
- `content/blog/hello-world.mdx` — sample post with bilingual frontmatter

**Created/fixed:**
- `components/blog/MDXRemote.tsx` — server component wrapper using `next-mdx-remote/rsc` with `remark-gfm` + `rehype-slug` plugins
- `types/mdx.d.ts` — type declarations for `next-mdx-remote/rsc`, `gray-matter`, `reading-time`, `rehype-slug`, `remark-gfm`
- Refactored `BlogPostPage.tsx` to accept rendered MDX as `children` (ReactNode) instead of raw source
- Refactored `[slug]/page.tsx` to render MDX server-side and extract TOC server-side

**Installed:**
- `gray-matter`, `reading-time`, `next-mdx-remote`, `@mdx-js/react`, `remark-gfm`, `rehype-slug`, `rehype-pretty-code`, `@types/mdx`

Build passes with the blog at `/blog` and the sample post at `/blog/hello-world`.

